{{Infobox football biography | name = Ali Mourade | image = | fullname = Ali Mourade | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1984|10|17|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Marseille]], [[France]] | height = {{height|m=1.90}} | position = [[Defender (football)|Defender]] | currentclub = FC La Sarraz-Ecläpens | clubnumber = | youthyears1 = |youthclubs1 = | years1 = 2003–2005 |clubs1 = [[Girondins Bordeaux|Bordeaux B]] |caps1 = |goals1 = | years2 = 2009– |clubs2 = FC La Sarraz-Ecläpens |caps2 = |goals2 = | nationalyears1 = 2011 | nationalteam1 = [[Comoros national football team|Comoros]] | nationalcaps1 = 3 | nationalgoals1 = 0 | pcupdate = 13 April 2018 | ntupdate = 6 January 2012 }}
'''Ali Mourade''' (born October 17, 1984, [[Marseille]], [[France]]) is a [[Comoro Islands|Comorian]] [[football (soccer)]] player who plays as a [[Defender (football)|Defender]]. He currently plays for FC La Sarraz-Ecläpens and the [[Comoros national football team]].
==Club career== In 2011, he signed with Swiss side FC La Sarraz-Ecläpens.<ref>{{cite web|author=A. Mourade |url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/ali-mourad/217162/ |title=Comoros - A. Mourade - Profile with news, career statistics and history |publisher=Soccerway |date=2011-11-15 |accessdate=2012-02-10}}</ref>
==International career== In 2011, he made his debut for the [[Comoros national football team]].<ref>{{NFT player|pid=44543|name=Ali Mourade|accessdate=2012-02-10}}</ref>
