{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Wavertree Road Ground | nickname = | country = England | image = | location = [[Liverpool]], [[Lancashire]] | establishment = 1847 | seating_capacity = | end1 = | end2 = | year3 = 1866 | club3 = [[Lancashire County Cricket Club|Lancashire]] | year2 = 1863 & 1872 | club2 = [[North of England cricket team|North]] | year1 = 1859 | club1 = [[Gentlemen of the North]] | date = 4 September | year = 2010 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/586.html profile }}
'''Wavertree Road Ground''' was a [[cricket]] ground in [[Liverpool]], [[Lancashire]]. The first recorded match on the ground was in 1847, when Liverpool played Birkenhead Park.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/586_misc.html Other matches played on Wavertree Road Ground]</ref>
In 1859, the ground held its first [[first-class cricket|first-class]] match when the [[Gentlemen of the North]] played the [[Gentlemen of the South]]. The next first-class match held on the ground came in 1863 when the [[North of England cricket team|North]] played the [[South of England cricket team|South]]. [[Lancashire County Cricket Club|Lancashire]] played a single first-class match there in 1866 against [[Surrey County Cricket Club|Surrey]]. The final first-class match there came in 1872 when the North played the South.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/586.html First-Class Matches played on Wavertree Road Ground]</ref>
The final recorded match held on the ground came in 1880 when Wavertree played the Gentlemen of Canada. Shortly after this match the ground was sold for development and built over.
